      <div xml:id="NA57-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu ceṟippaṟivuṟīiya (EN, ER, EV: aṟivuṟīi) varaivu kaṭāyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is asking for marriage in order to inform of [her] being put in confinement.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA57">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            taṭaṅkōṭ ṭāmāṉ maṭaṅkaṇ māniraik</l>
<l>            kuṉṟa vēṅkaik kaṉṟoṭu vatinteṉat</l>
<l>            tuñcupatam peṟṟa tuyttalai manti</l>
<l>            kalleṉac cuṟṟaṅ kaikaviyāk kuṟuki</l>
<l>            vīṅkucurai ñemuṅka vāṅkit tīmpāl </l>
<l>            kallā vaṉpaṟaḻk kainniṟai piḻiyu</l>
<l>            māmalai nāṭa maruṭkai yuṭaittē</l>
<l>            ceṅkōṟ koṭuṅkuraṟ ciṟutiṉai viyaṉpuṉaṅ</l>
<l>            koypataṅ kuṟukuṅ kālaiyem</l>
<l>            maiyī rōti māṇalan tolaivē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>O man from a land of big mountains where,</l>
<l rend="indent2">as the long row of broad-horned wild cows with innocent eyes</l>
<l rend="indent2">abided with the calves by the Vēṅkai trees on the hill,</l>
<l rend="indent">when the cotton-headed she-monkey,</l>
<l rend="indent3">that had taken the opportunity [they] were sleeping,</l>
<l rend="indent">comes near quietly, without passing [her] kinsfolk*s group(?)<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">kai kaviyā</term>: the point seems to be clear enough, that is, secrecy. Unfortunately, <term xml:lang="ta">kavi</term> seems to mean only "cover, surround", but if we take <term xml:lang="ta">kai</term> to mean "group" here, it might just about work.</note>,</l>
<l rend="indent">[and] bends [and] presses the swelling udder,</l>
<l rend="indent">the untaught strong young [monkey] presses out a handful of sweet milk,</l>
<l rend="indent4">– it is bewildering,</l>
<l rend="indent">the loss of glorious goodness in our kajal[-dark] moist hair,</l>
<l rend="indent2">at the moment when harvest time approaches</l>
<l rend="indent3">on the wide fields of small millet with red stalks [and] bent ears.</l>
    </lg>
